result.execSummary:
The defendant Jonathon C Campbell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Report to County Jail (<10 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.425(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court orders the cash bond on file be applied to the court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Huber.  Sentence is to commence within 60 days.  Court has no objection to the defendant serving the jail sentence in Milwaukee County, if it can be arranged and at no additional costs to Green Lake County.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY to the amended charge.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to the amended charge and orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Sentencing argument by DA.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Privat - requests sentence be served in Milwaukee County - requests three days of sentence credit.  NO statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to 30 days in the county jail - commence within sixty days - no objection to service of the sentence in Milwaukee County - grants 3 days of sentence credit - with huber.
